e and religion conceptualized the medieval past. Yet although later generations of scholarshave since approached their research from vantage points shaped by his arguments, few of his writings have been previously accessible to an Anglophone audience. This volume presents translations of six of Grundmann's most significant essays on the intertwined themes of medieval heresy, literacy, and inquisition. Together, they offer new access to Grundmann's scholarship, one which will catalyze new perspectives on the medieval religious past and enable a fresh consideration of his intellectual legacy in the twenty-first century. JENNIFER KOLPACOFF DEANE is Professor of History at the University of Minnesota, Morris.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChurch historyyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aHeresyxHistory. 0aInquisitionxHistory. 0aReligionxHistory. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aFrench literature.  aGerman literature.  aLatin literature.  achurch history.  adoctrine.  aecclesiastical.  aexegesis.  aheresy.  aheretic.  ainquisition.  alearning.  aliteracy.  amedieval Europe.  amedieval historiography.  amedieval religion.  aorthodoxy.  ascripture.  avernacular.1 aBorst, Arno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeane, Jennifer Kolpacoff, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311143102440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787447004?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787447004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787447004/original  a978-3-11-143102-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles